{{Infobox institute |name =Global Alliance to Prevent Prematurity and Stillbirth |image =File:GAPPS logo.png |image_name = |image_size = |image_alt = |caption = |latin_name = |motto = |founder = Craig E. Rubens, MD, PhD|established ={{Start date|2007}} |mission = |focus = |head_label = |head = |faculty = |adjunct_faculty = |staff = |key_people = |budget = |endowment = |debt = |num_members = |subsidiaries = |owner = |non-profit_slogan = Make every birth a healthy birth.|former_name = |location = |city =[[Seattle]] |state =[[Washington (state)|WA]] |country =USA |coor = |address =1100 Olive Way |website =[http://www.gapps.org/ gapps.org] |dissolved = |footnotes = }}
The '''Global Alliance to Prevent Prematurity and Stillbirth (GAPPS)''' was founded in 2007 as an initiative of [[Seattle Children’s]]. GAPPS’ mission is to lead a collaborative, global effort to increase awareness and accelerate innovative research and interventions that will improve [[maternal health|maternal]], newborn and child health outcomes around the world, with a focus on [[preterm birth]] and [[stillbirth]].<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.biomedcentral.com/1471-2393/10/S1/S7 |title=Global report on preterm birth and stillbirth |first= |last= |work=BMC Pregnancy & Childbirth|date=23 February 2010}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.gapps.org/index.php/about/mission_vision/ |title=Mission and Vision |work=GAPPS}}</ref>
==GAPPS Repository== The GAPPS Repository is a [[biobank]] of [[pregnancy]] specimens matched with data from patient questionnaires. It supports research on normal and abnormal pregnancies, including how pregnancy affects maternal and child health after [[childbirth|delivery]].<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.xconomy.com/seattle/2012/03/14/seattle-childrens-sets-up-rare-biobank-of-pregnancy-specimens/ |title=Seattle Children's Sets Up Rare Biobank to Study Premature Birth |work=Xconomy|date=14 March 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.who.int/pmnch/media/news/2012/20120410_gapps_biorepository/en/index.html |title=New biorepository to help uncover mysteries of pregnancy and childbirth |work=World Health Organization |date=10 April 2012}}</ref> The Repository is also available to researchers to study the [[fetal]] origins of persistent health problems like [[diabetes]], [[obesity]], and [[hypertension]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.fastcoexist.com/1680302/a-library-of-samples-from-pregnant-women-to-help-disease-research |title=A Library of Samples From Pregnant Women To Help Disease Research |work=Fast Company |date=6 August 2012}}</ref>
==Preventing Preterm Birth initiative== In November 2011 the [[Bill & Melinda Gates Foundation]] provided $20 million to GAPPS for the Preventing Preterm Birth initiative, part of the foundation's [[Grand Challenges in Global Health]]. The Preventing Preterm Birth initiative focuses on finding new interventions to prevent premature birth and stillbirth by limiting infection and improving nutrition.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.bizjournals.com/seattle/blog/2011/11/gates-foundation-awards-20m-for.html |title=Gates Foundation awards $20M for premature birth research |work=Puget Sound Business Journal |date=7 November 2011}}</ref>
